# Frontend Environment Variables for Production (Netlify)
# 
# IMPORTANT: Do NOT commit this file with actual values to version control
# This is a template file. Copy this as .env.production.local for local testing
# or set these variables directly in Netlify's dashboard under Site Settings > Environment Variables

# =============================================================================
# NETLIFY DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS:
# =============================================================================
# 1. Go to your Netlify site dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Site Settings > Environment Variables
# 3. Add the following environment variables:
# =============================================================================

# Backend API URL - REPLACE WITH YOUR ELASTIC BEANSTALK URL
# Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-app.us-east-1.elasticbeanstalk.com
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-url.elasticbeanstalk.com

# Optional: Enable production mode features
VITE_NODE_ENV=production

# Optional: Analytics and monitoring
# VITE_ANALYTICS_ID=your_analytics_id

# =============================================================================
# LOCAL TESTING (Optional)
# =============================================================================
# For local production testing, you can create .env.production.local with:
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080

# =============================================================================
# NOTES:
# =============================================================================
# - All frontend environment variables MUST be prefixed with VITE_
# - The backend URL should point to your Elastic Beanstalk environment
# - Make sure your backend CORS is configured to allow your Netlify domain
# - You can test the build locally with: npm run build && npm run preview